Stakeholder Analysis

Stakeholders are individuals or groups who have an interest in or are affected by the Blood Bank Management System. They are categorized as primary and secondary stakeholders.

Primary Stakeholders

Primary stakeholders are directly involved in using or managing the system.

Blood Bank Administrators

Manage donor records, blood inventory, and blood requests.

Responsible for system operation and decision-making.

Hospital Staff / Medical Professionals

Request required blood units during emergencies or surgeries.

Depend on real-time blood availability information.

Blood Donors

Register and update personal and donation details.

Receive notifications about donation eligibility and requests.

System Users (Authorized Staff)

Use the system for daily operations like data entry, updates, and monitoring.

Secondary Stakeholders

Secondary stakeholders are indirectly affected by the system.

Patients

Benefit from timely availability of safe blood during treatment and emergencies.

Healthcare Organizations

Gain improved coordination and efficiency in blood supply management.

Government and Regulatory Bodies

Monitor compliance with healthcare and blood safety regulations.

Project Guide / Faculty

Review project progress, provide guidance, and evaluate outcomes.

System Developers and Maintenance Team

Maintain, update, and enhance the system after deployment.

Summary

By addressing the needs of both primary and secondary stakeholders, the Blood Bank Management System ensures efficient operations, improved coordination, and better healthcare support.
